<!-- Page Hero (dark banner) -->
<div class="page-hero">
  <span class="section-label">Our Story</span>
  <h1 class="page-hero-title">Born in a small room in London</h1>
  <p class="page-hero-desc">MUNLER began with two people, very little space, and one refusal: that a mirror should ever be ordinary.</p>
</div>

<!-- Chapter 1: image left -->
<section class="about-story">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-story-grid">
      <div class="about-story-img reveal">
        <img src="{{ 'about-1.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="The London skyline at dusk, where MUNLER began">
      </div>
      <div class="about-story-text reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Chapter One</span>
        <h2>It started on a building site</h2>
        <p>Before MUNLER, there was a building site. One of us trained as a civil engineer and spent years in London on large, demanding projects, the kind where materials are chosen for how they perform, not for how little they cost.</p>
        <p>That world teaches you to look closely at how things are made, and to trust the materials that earn it. It is a habit we never lost.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Chapter 2: image right -->
<section class="about-story">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-story-grid">
      <div class="about-story-text reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Chapter Two</span>
        <h2>Every mirror looked the same</h2>
        <p>Somewhere along the way, one thing would not let go. Every mirror looked the same. The same safe shapes, the same thin aluminium and pot metal, the same quiet compromise. For something you stand in front of every single day, it felt like a missed opportunity.</p>
        <p>We became convinced a mirror could be the opposite of forgettable. Sculptural, asymmetrical, finished to a standard no one else seemed willing to reach. The asymmetry was deliberate, a quiet refusal of all that sameness.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-story-img reveal">
        <img src="{{ 'about-2.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="A quiet London street on a grey morning">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Chapter 3: image left -->
<section class="about-story">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-story-grid">
      <div class="about-story-img reveal">
        <img src="{{ 'about-3.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="A misty path through a London park">
      </div>
      <div class="about-story-text reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Chapter Three</span>
        <h2>Ten square metres</h2>
        <p>MUNLER was not born in a studio or a boardroom. It was born in a ten square metre room in London, where we were living at the time. We were twenty eight and twenty four.</p>
        <p>We left a career behind and put everything into this idea, in conditions that were anything but comfortable. Looking back, that small room was the whole point. MUNLER came out of scarcity, out of the will to build something lasting from very little.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Chapter 4: image right -->
<section class="about-story">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-story-grid">
      <div class="about-story-text reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Chapter Four</span>
        <h2>Two different worlds</h2>
        <p>We come from two different worlds. One from engineering and the building trade, the other from international relations and law. What we share is a stubborn belief that things should be made properly, and a willingness to risk a great deal to prove it.</p>
        <p>We are partners in life as well as in work, and we built MUNLER together, from that first room.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="about-story-img reveal">
        <img src="{{ 'about-4.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="A London mews at golden hour">
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Chapter 5: image left -->
<section class="about-story">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-story-grid">
      <div class="about-story-img reveal">
        <img src="{{ 'about-5.jpg' | asset_url }}" alt="An elegant London street in Mayfair">
      </div>
      <div class="about-story-text reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Chapter Five</span>
        <h2>Made properly, or not at all</h2>
        <p>To make mirrors properly, we went looking for people who still cared about making things properly. We spoke with manufacturers across the world and chose only those who could meet our standard.</p>
        <p>Premium stainless steel, ecological silver glass that is copper free and lead free, and a level of finish you can feel. Two things are never for sale here: quality and responsibility.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- Chapter 6: image right -->
<section class="about-story">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-story-grid">
      <div class="about-story-text reveal">
        <span class="section-label">Chapter Six</span>
        <h2>That is a MUNLER</h2>
        <p>The name is personal. It is ours, kept deliberately quiet, a signature rather than a spotlight. We have always preferred to let the work speak.</p>
        <p>Our hope is a simple one. That one day someone could walk into a room, glance at the mirror on the wall, and simply know. That is a MUNLER.</p>
